transportation.name: Sydney Trains Network T8 Airport & South Line
transportation.description: Macarthur to City via Airport or Sydenham

infos.urlText: Weekend trackwork: Buses replace trains between Glenfield and Sydenham
infos.content:
Saturday 15 and Sunday 16 December
  • Buses replace trains between Glenfield and Sydenham.
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between:
    - Macarthur and the City via Granville
    - Campbelltown and Central, platforms 1-12, via Regents Park
    - Turrella and the City via the Airport
    - Sydenham and the City
  • If you are travelling from the City to stations Bardwell Park to Holsworthy, catch a T3 Bankstown or
    T4 Eastern Suburbs & Illawarra Line train to Sydenham and change for a bus.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus routes
22T8: Glenfield, then all stations to Padstow, then Sydenham and return
23T8: East Hills, then all stations to Turrella, then Wolli Creek, Sydenham and return
24T8: Glenfield, then all stations to Kingsgrove (except Holsworthy), then Sydenham and return
25T8: Glenfield, then Sydenham and return
infos.subtitle: Weekend trackwork: Buses replace trains between Glenfield and Sydenham

properties.speechText: Saturday 15th and Sunday 16th December buses replace trains between Glenfield and Sydenham. Trains run to a changed timetable between and stopping pattern. See transport N.S.W. for info for full details.
